@jeking3 I think a better alternative could be the 'long' package https://www.npmjs.com/package/long. Bigint would allow results to be non-Longs. 

The reason we kept the original node-int64 was that, we wanted to avoid breaking client code. Thrift was already using node-int64.

A less disruptive change would be to add a toBignum() method to Int64.

